msgid "27. Mahāpesakārasikkhāpada"
msgstr "27. The long training rule on weavers"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.27.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.145"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2362"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena aññataro puriso pavāsaṃ gacchanto pajāpatiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "At that time a man who was going away said to his wife,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.3"
msgid ""
"“suttaṃ dhārayitvā amukassa tantavāyassa dehi, cīvaraṃ vāyāpetvā nikkhipa,"
msgstr ""
"“Weigh some thread, take it to the weavers, get them to weave robe-cloth, "
"and put the robe-cloth aside."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "āgato ayyaṃ upanandaṃ cīvarena acchādessāmī”ti."
msgstr "When I return I’ll give it to Venerable Upananda.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.5"
msgid ""
"Assosi kho aññataro piṇḍacāriko bhikkhu tassa purisassa imaṃ vācaṃ "
"bhāsamānassa."
msgstr "A monk who was an alms-collector heard that man speaking those words."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu yenāyasmā upanando sakyaputto tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "He then went to Upananda"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "“mahāpuññosi tvaṃ, āvuso upananda,"
msgstr "“Upananda, you have much merit."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "amukasmiṃ okāse aññataro puriso pavāsaṃ gacchanto pajāpatiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr ""
"In such-and-such a place I heard a man, as he was about to go away, tell his "
"wife"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.10"
msgid ""
"‘suttaṃ dhārayitvā amukassa tantavāyassa dehi, cīvaraṃ vāyāpetvā nikkhipa, "
"āgato ayyaṃ upanandaṃ cīvarena acchādessāmī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"to get robe-cloth woven so that he could give it to you when he returned.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "“Atthāvuso, maṃ so upaṭṭhāko”ti."
msgstr "“He’s my supporter.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "Sopi kho tantavāyo āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa upaṭṭhāko hoti."
msgstr "And the weaver was Upananda’s supporter too."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.258"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2363"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto yena so tantavāyo tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Upananda then went to that weaver"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā taṃ tantavāyaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "“idaṃ kho, āvuso, cīvaraṃ maṃ uddissa viyyati;"
msgstr "“This robe-cloth that you’re weaving for me,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "āyatañca karohi vitthatañca."
msgstr "make it long and wide."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.146"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.17"
msgid ""
"Appitañca suvītañca suppavāyitañca suvilekhitañca suvitacchitañca karohī”ti."
msgstr ""
"And make it closely woven, well-woven, well-stretched, well-scraped, and "
"well-combed.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "“Ete kho me, bhante, suttaṃ dhārayitvā adaṃsu;"
msgstr ""
"“Venerable, they’ve already weighed the thread and given it to me, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "iminā suttena cīvaraṃ vināhī”ti."
msgstr "‘Weave the robe-cloth with this thread.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.20"
msgid "“Na, bhante, sakkā āyataṃ vā vitthataṃ vā appitaṃ vā kātuṃ."
msgstr "I won’t be able to make it long, wide, or closely woven."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.21"
msgid ""
"Sakkā ca kho, bhante, suvītañca suppavāyitañca suvilekhitañca "
"suvitacchitañca kātun”ti."
msgstr ""
"But I’m able to make it well-woven, well-stretched, well-scraped, and well-"
"combed.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.22"
msgid "“Iṅgha tvaṃ, āvuso, āyatañca karohi vitthatañca appitañca."
msgstr "“Just make it long, wide, and closely woven."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.23"
msgid "Na tena suttena paṭibaddhaṃ bhavissatī”ti."
msgstr "There won’t be any lack of thread.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2364"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.24"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so tantavāyo yathābhataṃ suttaṃ tante upanetvā yena sā itthī "
"tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"Then, when all the thread had been used up, that weaver went to that woman"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.25"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā taṃ itthiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.26"
msgid "“suttena, ayye, attho”ti."
msgstr "“Madam, I need more thread.”"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: ayyo → ayya (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.27"
msgid "“Nanu tvaṃ ayyo mayā vutto—"
msgstr "“But, sir, didn’t I tell you"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.28"
msgid "‘iminā suttena cīvaraṃ vināhī’”ti."
msgstr "to weave the robe-cloth with that thread?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.29"
msgid "“Saccāhaṃ, ayye, tayā vutto—"
msgstr "“You did."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.30"
msgid "‘iminā suttena cīvaraṃ vināhī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.31"
msgid "Api ca maṃ ayyo upanando evamāha—"
msgstr "But Venerable Upananda told me"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.32"
msgid "‘iṅgha tvaṃ, āvuso, āyatañca karohi vitthatañca appitañca,"
msgstr "to make it long, wide, and closely woven."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.33"
msgid "na tena suttena paṭibaddhaṃ bhavissatī’”ti."
msgstr "And he said there wouldn’t be any lack of thread.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.34"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sā itthī yattakaṃyeva suttaṃ paṭhamaṃ adāsi tattakaṃ pacchā adāsi."
msgstr ""
"That woman then gave him as much thread again as she had done the first time."

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.147"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.35"
msgid "Assosi kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto—"
msgstr "Soon Upananda heard"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.36"
msgid "“so kira puriso pavāsato āgato”ti."
msgstr "that that man had returned from his travels,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.37"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto yena tassa purisassa nivesanaṃ "
"tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "and he went to his house"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.38"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "and sat down on a prepared seat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.39"
msgid "Atha kho so puriso yenāyasmā upanando sakyaputto tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "That man approached him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.40"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.41"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so puriso pajāpatiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "He then said to his wife,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.42"
msgid "“vītaṃ taṃ cīvaran”ti?"
msgstr "“Has the robe-cloth been woven?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.43"
msgid "“Āmāyya, vītaṃ taṃ cīvaran”ti."
msgstr "“Yes it has.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.44"
msgid "“Āhara, ayyaṃ upanandaṃ cīvarena acchādessāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Please bring it, I’ll give it to Venerable Upananda.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.45"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sā itthī taṃ cīvaraṃ nīharitvā sāmikassa datvā etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr ""
"She then got the robe-cloth, gave it to her husband, and told him what had "
"happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.46"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so puriso āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa cīvaraṃ datvā "
"ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "After giving the robe-cloth to Upananda, he grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.47"
msgid "“mahicchā ime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā asantuṭṭhā."
msgstr "“These Sakyan ascetics have great desires; they’re not content."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.48"
msgid "Nayime sukarā cīvarena acchādetuṃ."
msgstr "It’s no easy matter to give them robe-cloth."

#. VAR: upanando mayā pubbe appavārito tantavāye → gahapatikassa tantavāye (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.49"
msgid ""
"Kathañhi nāma ayyo upanando mayā pubbe appavārito tantavāye upasaṅkamitvā "
"cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjissatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"How could Venerable Upananda go to the weavers and specify the kind of robe-"
"cloth he wanted without first being invited by me?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2365"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.50"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa purisassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of that man,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.51"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.52"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized Upananda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.53"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto pubbe appavārito gahapatikassa "
"tantavāye upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjissatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“How can Venerable Upananda go to a lay person’s weavers and specify the "
"kind of robe-cloth he wants without first being invited?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.259"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2366"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.54"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ anekapariyāyena "
"vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing him in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.55"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, pubbe appavārito gahapatikassa tantavāye "
"upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Upananda, that you did this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.56"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.57"
msgid "“Ñātako te, upananda, aññātako”ti?"
msgstr "“Is he a relative of yours?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.58"
msgid "“Aññātako, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“No, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.59"
msgid ""
"“Aññātako, moghapurisa, aññātakassa na jānāti patirūpaṃ vā appatirūpaṃ vā "
"santaṃ vā asantaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"“Foolish man, people who are not related don’t know what’s appropriate and "
"what’s inappropriate in dealing with each other, what’s right and what’s "
"wrong."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.148"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.60"
msgid ""
"Tattha nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, pubbe appavārito aññātakassa gahapatikassa "
"tantavāye upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjissasi."
msgstr ""
"And still you went to the weavers of an unrelated lay person and specified "
"the kind of robe-cloth you wanted without first being invited."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.61"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.62"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.62a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2367"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.63"
msgid ""
"“Bhikkhuṃ paneva uddissa aññātako gahapati vā gahapatānī vā tantavāyehi "
"cīvaraṃ vāyāpeyya, tatra ce so bhikkhu pubbe appavārito tantavāye "
"upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjeyya—"
msgstr ""
"‘If a layman or laywoman is getting robe-cloth woven by weavers for an "
"unrelated monk and, without first being invited, that monk goes to those "
"weavers and specifies the kind of robe-cloth he wants, saying,"

#. VAR: viyyati → vīyati (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.64"
msgid "‘idaṃ kho, āvuso, cīvaraṃ maṃ uddissa viyyati."
msgstr "‘Sirs, this robe-cloth that you are weaving for me,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.65"
msgid "Āyatañca karotha vitthatañca."
msgstr "make it long and wide;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.66"
msgid ""
"Appitañca suvītañca suppavāyitañca suvilekhitañca suvitacchitañca karotha."
msgstr ""
"make it closely woven, well-woven, well-stretched, well-scraped, and well-"
"combed;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.67"
msgid "Appeva nāma mayampi āyasmantānaṃ kiñcimattaṃ anupadajjeyyāmā’ti."
msgstr "and perhaps I will even give you a small gift;’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.68"
msgid ""
"Evañca so bhikkhu vatvā kiñcimattaṃ anupadajjeyya antamaso "
"piṇḍapātamattampi, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"then, in saying that and afterwards giving them a small gift, even if it is "
"only a bit of almsfood, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and "
"confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs1.69"
msgid "(<em>27</em>:<strong>46</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.27.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2368"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.1"
msgid "Bhikkhuṃ paneva uddissāti"
msgstr "For a […] monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "bhikkhussatthāya bhikkhuṃ ārammaṇaṃ karitvā bhikkhuṃ acchādetukāmo."
msgstr ""
"for the benefit of a monk; making a monk the object, he wishes to give to "
"the monk."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2369"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "Aññātako nāma"
msgstr "Unrelated:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.4"
msgid "mātito vā pitito vā yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā asambaddho."
msgstr ""
"anyone who is not a descendant of one’s male ancestors going back seven "
"generations, either on the mother’s side or on the father’s side."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2370"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.5"
msgid "Gahapati nāma"
msgstr "A layman:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "yo koci agāraṃ ajjhāvasati."
msgstr "any man who lives in a house."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2071"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "Gahapatānī nāma"
msgstr "A laywoman:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.8"
msgid "yā kāci agāraṃ ajjhāvasati."
msgstr "any woman who lives in a house."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2372"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.9"
msgid "Tantavāyehīti"
msgstr "By weavers:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "pesakārehi."
msgstr "by those who weave."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2373"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.11"
msgid "Cīvaraṃ nāma"
msgstr "Robe-cloth:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. The six are linen, cotton, silk, wool, sunn hemp, and hemp; see <ref>Mv.8.3.1</ref>.
#. This means not smaller than 8 by 4 standard (<i lang="pli">sugata</i>) finger-breadths, or 16 by 8 cm; see <ref>Kkh.94.4</ref> and BMC I, pp.565-566.</span>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.12"
msgid "channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ vikappanupagaṃ pacchimaṃ."
msgstr ""
"one of the six kinds of robe-cloth, but not smaller than what can be "
"transferred."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.149"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2374"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.13"
msgid "Vāyāpeyyāti"
msgstr "Is getting […] woven:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.14"
msgid "vināpeti."
msgstr "is causing to weave."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2375"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.15"
msgid "Tatra ce so bhikkhūti"
msgstr "If […] that monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.16"
msgid "yaṃ bhikkhuṃ uddissa cīvaraṃ viyyati so bhikkhu."
msgstr "the monk for whom the robe-cloth is being woven."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2376"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.17"
msgid "Pubbe appavāritoti"
msgstr "Without first being invited:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.18"
msgid "pubbe avutto hoti—"
msgstr "without it first being said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.19"
msgid "“kīdisena te, bhante, cīvarena attho,"
msgstr "“Venerable, what kind of robe-cloth do you need?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.20"
msgid "kīdisaṃ te cīvaraṃ vāyāpemī”ti?"
msgstr "What kind of robe-cloth should I get woven for you?”"

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2377"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.21"
msgid "Tantavāye upasaṅkamitvāti"
msgstr "Goes to those weavers:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.22"
msgid "gharaṃ gantvā yattha katthaci upasaṅkamitvā."
msgstr "having gone to their house or having gone wherever."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2378"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.23"
msgid "Cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjeyyāti—"
msgstr "Specifies the kind of robe-cloth he wants:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.24"
msgid ""
"“idaṃ kho, āvuso, cīvaraṃ maṃ uddissa viyyati, āyatañca karotha vitthatañca."
msgstr ""
"“Sirs, this robe-cloth that you are weaving for me, make it long and wide;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.25"
msgid ""
"Appitañca suvītañca suppavāyitañca suvilekhitañca suvitacchitañca karotha."
msgstr ""
"make it closely woven, well-woven, well-stretched, well-scraped, and well-"
"combed;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.26"
msgid "Appeva nāma mayampi āyasmantānaṃ kiñcimattaṃ anupadajjeyyāmā”ti."
msgstr "and perhaps I will even give you a small gift.”"

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.260"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2379"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.27"
msgid ""
"Evañca so bhikkhu vatvā kiñcimattaṃ anupadajjeyya antamaso "
"piṇḍapātamattampīti."
msgstr ""
"Then in saying that and afterwards giving them a small gift, even if it is "
"only a bit of almsfood—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.28"
msgid "Piṇḍapāto nāma"
msgstr "Almsfood:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.29"
msgid ""
"yāgupi bhattampi khādanīyampi cuṇṇapiṇḍopi dantakaṭṭhampi dasikasuttampi, "
"antamaso dhammampi bhaṇati."
msgstr ""
"rice-porridge, a meal, non-staple food, bath powder, a toothbrush, a piece "
"of thread, and even if he gives a teaching."

#. </span></p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2380"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.30"
msgid ""
"Tassa vacanena āyataṃ vā vitthataṃ vā appitaṃ vā karoti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If the weaver makes it long or wide or closely woven because of the monk’s "
"statement, then for the act of speaking, he commits an offense of wrong "
"conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.31"
msgid "Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When he gets the robe-cloth, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.32"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr ""
"The robe-cloth should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.33"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.34"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""
"To be expanded as in <a class=\"cr\" href=\"./pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#13\">"
"Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17</a>, with appropriate substitutions. …"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.35"
msgid ""
"“idaṃ me, bhante, cīvaraṃ pubbe appavārito aññātakassa gahapatikassa "
"tantavāye upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpannaṃ nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Venerables, this robe-cloth for which I went to the weavers of an unrelated "
"lay person and specified the kind of robe-cloth I wanted without first being "
"invited is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.36"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.37"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.38"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.39"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this robe-cloth back to you.’”"

#. </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.39a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.150"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2381"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.40"
msgid ""
"Aññātake aññātakasaññī pubbe appavārito gahapatikassa tantavāye "
"upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjati, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If the lay person is unrelated and the monk perceives them as unrelated and, "
"without first being invited, he approaches the lay person’s weavers and "
"specifies the kind of robe-cloth he wants, he commits an offense entailing "
"relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.41"
msgid ""
"Aññātake vematiko pubbe appavārito gahapatikassa tantavāye upasaṅkamitvā "
"cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjati, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If the lay person is unrelated, but the monk is unsure if they are and, "
"without first being invited, he approaches the lay person’s weavers and "
"specifies the kind of robe-cloth he wants, he commits an offense entailing "
"relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.42"
msgid ""
"Aññātake ñātakasaññī pubbe appavārito gahapatikassa tantavāye upasaṅkamitvā "
"cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjati, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If the lay person is unrelated, but the monk perceives them as related and, "
"without first being invited, he approaches the lay person’s weavers and "
"specifies the kind of robe-cloth he wants, he commits an offense entailing "
"relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2382"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.43"
msgid "Ñātake añātakasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the lay person is related, but the monk perceives them as unrelated, he "
"commit an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.44"
msgid "Ñātake vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the lay person is related, but the monk is unsure if they are, he commit "
"an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.45"
msgid "Ñātake ñātakasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If the lay person is related and the monk perceives them as related, there "
"is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.45a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2383"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.46"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.47"
msgid "ñātakānaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is from relatives;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.48"
msgid "pavāritānaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is from those who have given an invitation;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.49"
msgid "aññassatthāya,"
msgstr "if it is for the benefit of someone else;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.50"
msgid "attano dhanena,"
msgstr "if it is by means of his own property;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.51"
msgid "mahagghaṃ vāyāpetukāmassa appagghaṃ vāyāpeti,"
msgstr ""
"if someone wants to get expensive robe-cloth woven, but he gets them to "
"weave inexpensive robe-cloth instead;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.52"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.53"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2384"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np27:pts-cs2.54"
msgid "Mahāpesakārasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ."
msgstr "The seventh rule, the long training rule on weavers, is finished."

